description:
Space is LOCKABLE & ENTIRELY PRIVATE!!!

You’ll LOVE your Temporary Home because of it's Multicultural Urban Environment; easily 'Walk-Able' to all Manner of Parks, Museums & Hospitals. Newly Renovated & Accessible to both the #2/5 Subway Line and #B44 Bus Line, Covering all of Manhattan & Brooklyn within Minutes!  You'll also Appreciate its Natural Amenities for Couples, Children & Solo Adventurers. A+++

Exceedingly few short-term guest suites are entirely private, and almost none offer a full kitchen . We believe you will be thrilled, and it's all newly refurbished to boot!

NOTE: Although the sofa bed is listed by AirBnB as 'common space', it is located fully within your completely *PRIVATE* accommodation.

Private & separately accessed/keyed: Living Room, Bedroom, Bathroom, Kitchen, Veranda...all the safety & comforts of your own Home.

We are phone accessible during most all daylight hours, and in an appropriately urgent situation, we can be physically present as well.

Very nearby gardens and parks (amenities galore), restaurants, two hospitals, museums, and every other entertainment available in Gotham City.

There is on-street parking in front/nearby our home, as well as public subway and bus access within mere blocks. Easily walk-able in all respects.

Guests are legally/financially responsible for ALL city regulations

Our place is like having a 2nd home in one of the largest Metropolises in the world, with the added attraction of a fully detached house in a genuine neighborhood. With Wi-Fi, basic cable TV and cooking at home...what's a good reason to triple your costs at a hotel?

hosts.about:
Dear Kindred  Spirits,

I LOVE to travel myself (Europe, The Caribbean, and MORE), so I know how important it is for travel arrangements to go smoothly. You are simply going to LOVE having your own place in the heart of New York City, one of the greatest cities in the world...with all the access to entertainment, business, and personal needs and desires that it represents.

I'm a professional white collar mom with children, and understand the importance of cleanliness, promptness, and essential expectations, along with basic respect and friendliness for others and their property, so I offer those to you and very much appreciate the same values in return. My goal is to provide you a safe, comfortable and enjoyable 'home away'. A home that you will return to again and again over the years!

Give me a shout and reach out! We'll both be so happy you did... 

Cheers and best,

Candy

review.comments: Brooklyn is a little out of the way if you're spending your days in the city, but it's super close to the subway. No better way to get a realistic NYC experience than to commute in every morning. 10/10 would stay here again or recommend to a friend.
